<font color="#FF0000">A LOVE LETTER TO ED FROM MOM</font><br>
<tt>Mon Nov 17 13:57:44 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Ed, <br>
Ok, so you want to make fun of maureens, I wasn't going to show you mom's letter, I receive a copy of the note she was thinking of sending you. <br><br>
Sorry mom had to share it.<br>
 <br><br>
A Letter From Mom to Ed...<br><br>
My Dear Favorite Son Ed, <br><br>
I'm writing this slow because I know you can't read fast. <br><br>
We don't live where we did when you first left. Your Dad read in the newspaper that most accidents happen within 20 miles of home, so we moved. <br><br>
I won't be able to send you the address as the last family here took the numbers with them for their next house, so they wouldn't have to change their address. <br><br>
This place has a washing machine. The first day I put four shirts in, pulled the chain, and I haven't seen them since. <br><br>
It only rained twice this week, three days the first time, and four days this time, When it rained Sunday, I forgot to tell TS it was raining and he went out to play and got struck by lighting.<br><br>
Cookie’s Marine Corps coat you wanted me to send to you, your brother Art said it would be a little too heavy to send in the mail with the heavy buttons, so we cut them off and put them in the pockets. <br><br>
About your sister Class lass, she had a baby this morning but I haven't found out what it is yet, so I don't know if you're an aunt or an uncle. If the baby is a girl your sister is going to name it after me; she's going to call it Mom. <br><br>
John locked his keys in the car yesterday. We were worried because it took him two hours to get me and my corpsmen friend out. <br><br>
Uncle Paul, who you call little PP, fell in a whiskey vat last week. Some man tried to pull him out but he fought them off and drowned. We had him cremated and he burned for <br>
three days. <br><br>
Three of your friends went off a bridge in a pick-up truck. Tom was driving. He rolled down the window and swam to safety. Your two friends, Gary and Bob were in the back. They drowned because they couldn't get the tailgate down. <br><br>
There isn't much more news at this time. Nothing much has happened.. write soon <br><br>
Love, Mom <br><br>
P.S. Anymouse,  was going to send you some money but the envelope was already sealed. <br>

